The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Saturday, December 13, 2003 				 Berlusconis jarring joke
																								Brussels, Dec. 12 (Reuters): Italian Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconis wisecrack jarred at the summit when he joked about being thrown from a helicopter.																								Polish Prime Minister Leszek Miller, who broke his spine in a helicopter crash, arrived in a wheelchair shortly after Berlusconi cracked the joke.																								The Italian leader joked that he and his wife were flying over a crowd of protesters. He told her: I could throw out one 10,000 euro note and make one person happy. I could throw two 5,000 euro notes and make two people happy. Or I could throw 10,000 one-euro coins and make 10,000 people happy. The helicopter pilot, he said, replied: We could throw you out and make everyone happy. 
